claim.claim-text:
1. A retaining wall structure for soil stabilization of earthen slopes and embankments, comprising: 
(a) a plurality of courses of cementatious blocks stacked together to define a retaining wall; 
(b) a backfill material provided behind the retaining wall; 
(c) a first layer of geotextile material defining a leading edge and a trailing edge, and having the leading edge disposed between vertically adjacent blocks at a predetermined vertical height of the retaining wall, and the trailing edge extending laterally backward therefrom into the backfill material such that the layer is engaged by the backfill material; and 
(d) a second layer of geotextile material provided so as to overlay and to contact the first layer of geotextile material from the leading edge thereof to at least a medial portion thereof between the leading edge and the trailing edge; 
whereby a high strength connection between the retaining wall and the backfill material is provided.

24. A method for forming a retaining wall structure for mechanically stabilized earth, comprising the steps of: 
(a) stacking together a plurality of courses of cementatious blocks to define a retaining wall; 
(b) providing a backfill material behind the retaining wall; 
(c) providing a first layer of geogrid web material having a leading edge and a trailing edge, and positioning the leading edge between vertically adjacent blocks at a predetermined vertical height of the retaining wall, and positioning the trailing edge to extend laterally backward therefrom into the backfill material such that the layer is engaged by the backfill material; and 
(d) providing a second layer of geogrid web material and positioning the second layer of geogrid web material so as to overlay and to contact the first layer of geogrid web material from the leading edge thereof to at least a medial portion thereof between the leading edge and the trailing edge thereof; 
whereby a retaining wall structure having a high strength connection between the retaining wall and backfill material therebehind is constructed.
